{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c1c7f4a8-7f4b-43b1-ac70-2bc5496d55e3","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2**, the modern approach is:\n\n1. **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (not the legacy static property)\n2. **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task` natively\n3. **Constructor** — use for synchronous setup\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Sync init: use the constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // other sync setup...\n    }\n\n    // Async init: use [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup work...\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** handles sync init + `TestContext` injection in one place.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** is the right place for `async` setup — it runs before each test.\n- Avoid the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` static-property pattern; constructor injection is the MSTest v3 way.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2573d838-724c-481d-b464-1f3ee0765119","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended patterns are:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: In MSTest v3+, `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (preferred) rather than using the old static property pattern.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: In MSTest v3+, `[TestInitialize]` methods can be `async Task`.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the modern recommended approach.\n\nIn MSTest 3.x:\n\n\n- `TestContext` gets injected directly through the constructor\n- `[TestInitialize]` can be marked as `async Task` for asynchronous setup\n- You'd typically use a single `[TestInitialize]` method, whether sync or async, rather than mixing both","outputTokens":532,"requestId":"105F:B86C3:2D7E85C:328E9F3:6A02ED00"},"id":"f487d96f-75a0-4768-aa50-d93ebd41b254","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:04:14.538Z","parentId":"1898c4ab-89b8-4d4e-9e22-21b58c7e4d88"}
